The '''Richard Dawkins Award''' is an annual award presented by the [[Atheist Alliance of America]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://atheistallianceamerica.org/the-richard-dawkins-award/|title=The Richard Dawkins Award|website=SERVING THE ATHEIST COMMUNITY FOR MORE THAN 20 YEARS|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref> to individuals it judges to have raised the public consciousness of atheism. It has been presented since 2003, and is named after [[Richard Dawkins]], an English evolutionary biologist who was named the world's top thinker in a 2013 reader's poll of the Prospect Magazine.<ref name=theguardian.com>{{cite web|title=Richard Dawkins named world's top thinker in poll|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/booksblog/2013/apr/25/richard-dawkins-named-top-thinker|publisher=theguardian.com|accessdate=6 October 2013}}</ref>
==Recipients== *2003: [[James Randi]] *2004: [[Ann Druyan]] *2005: [[Penn & Teller]] *2006: [[Julia Sweeney]] *2007: [[Daniel Dennett]] *2008: [[Ayaan Hirsi Ali]] *2009: [[Bill Maher]]<ref name="scienceblogs.com - Bill Maher">{{cite web|title=Bill Maher gets the Richard Dawkins Award? That’s like Jenny McCarthy getting an award for public health|url=http://scienceblogs.com/insolence/2009/07/23/bill-maher-gets-the-richard-dawkins-awar/|publisher=scienceblogs.com|accessdate=6 October 2013}}</ref> *2010: [[Susan Jacoby]]<ref name="skepticink - Susan Jacoby">{{cite web|title=Inspiring Women of TAM 2013: Susan Jacoby|url=http://www.skepticink.com/gps/2013/06/26/inspiring-women-of-tam-2013-susan-jacoby/|publisher=skepticink.com|accessdate=6 October 2013}}</ref> *2011: [[Christopher Hitchens]]<ref name="theguardian.com - Christopher H">{{cite web|title=Christopher Hitchens: one man's service in the war against delusion|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/dec/18/christopher-hitchens-atheism-dawkins-award-speech|publisher=theguardian.com|accessdate=6 October 2013}}</ref> *2012: [[Eugenie Scott]]<ref name="richarddawkins.net - Eugenie Scot">{{cite web|title=2012 Richard Dawkins Award for Eugenie Scott|url=http://www.richarddawkins.net/news_articles/2012/9/2/2012-richard-dawkins-award-for-eugenie-scott/|publisher=richarddawkins.net}}</ref> *2013: [[Steven Pinker]]<ref name=atheistallianceamerica>{{cite web|title=Dr. Steven Pinker to Receive 2013 Richard Dawkins Award |url=http://atheistallianceamerica.org/index.php/press-releases |publisher=atheistallianceamerica.org |accessdate=6 October 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513075127/http://atheistallianceamerica.org/index.php/press-releases |archivedate=May 13, 2013 }}</ref> *2014: [[Rebecca Goldstein]]<ref>http://secularsites.net/AAA-live/richard-dawkins-award-presentation/{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> *2015: [[Jerry Coyne]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://atheistallianceamerica.org/articles/jerry-coyne-receives-2015-richard-dawkins-award/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-03-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306213612/http://atheistallianceamerica.org/articles/jerry-coyne-receives-2015-richard-dawkins-award/ |archivedate=2015-03-06 |df= }}</ref> *2016: [[Lawrence M. Krauss]] *2017: [[David Silverman (activist)|David Silverman]] *2018: [[Stephen Fry]] [https://www.patheos.com/blogs/thinkingrationally/2018/10/wit-is-educated-insolence-the-richard-dawkins-award-stephen-fry-mark-gura-and-cw-brown - Read More] [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7LpOCcRALHI&feature=youtu.be - Watch Video]
